New health facilities like the Anglo Gold Ashanti Hospital in Carletonville have been left under-utilised or not used at all despite Gauteng battling a third wave. #eNCA Courtesy JOHANNESBURG - Despite the crisis in Gauteng, the province has new health facilities left under-utilised or not used at all. These include the Anglo Gold Ashanti Hospital in Carletonville on the West Rand. READ: COVID-19 in SA: 13,155 new cases, 112 deaths South Africa currently has recorded 13,155 new infections bringing the total cases to over 1.8-million. The country was placed under Alert Level 3 lockdown to help with the surge in cases.